comments.value: #This feature will validate the Add sell order side tray functionalities

elements.name: Validate the Place an order button on PV Screen for the portfolios which is up-to-date

steps.name: user is on Hive DashBoard screen
user selects any portfolio from portfolio dropdown which is up-to-date
page should be navigated to selected Portfolio summary screen and ‘Place an Order’ button should be enabled on PV screen

elements.name: Validate the Place order side tray

steps.name: user is on Portfolio screen
the user clicks the ‘Place an order’ button
place order side tray should open
place order, portfolio dropdown should be pre-populated the selected portfolio tab

elements.name: Validate the search portfolio from side tray

steps.name: user is on place an order side tray
user clicks the portfolio dropdown in `place an order` side tray
user should be able to search different portfolios from the portfolio dropdown
user is on place an order side tray
the user clicks the sell order button
‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray should be display

elements.name: Validate the cancel button in extended side tray

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user clicks the cancel button from the extended side tray
extended side tray should be closed and the user should navigate back to place order side tray
user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
user search for any portfolio holding using the searchbox
user should get the result based on the search keyword and select the portfolio_holding
user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
user finds the availble exit price of that portfolio holding on extended side tray
available exit price for that unit should be displayed with est.label

elements.name: Validate the Order amount field on add sell order screen

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user clicks anywhere in the screen without entering anything on the order amount field
error message should be displayed under the order amount screen

elements.name: Validate the order amount field validation

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user enters the Special character and text values in the order amount text box
user should not be allowed to enter the special character and text values into the order amount field

elements.name: Validate the add button on the ‘add a sell order button’

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user didn’t enter/select anything on the screen
‘Add’ button should be in disable mode
user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user enters more than available units
error message should be displayed under the order amount text box

elements.name: validate order amount and available units are the same

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user enter the enters the order amount which is equal to available units
user should get the 'Full redemption' message under the order value text box

comments.value: #	Scenario: validate the Minimum order amount
#	Given user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
#	When the order value is less than the transaction fee
#	Then user should not allow placing the order and error message should be displayed on the screen and +add or update button should be disabled

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user enters the order units
order units should be multiplied with the exit price and the result should be subtracted with a transaction fee
Final calculated value should be displayed as order value est with 2 decimal places

elements.name: Validate the Advice given ’No’ radio button

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
user select the ’No’ option
'Advice given' details should not be displayed

elements.name: validate the Advice given ‘Yes’ radio button

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
user select the ’Yes’ option
advice reason, date, summary and advice method fields should be display under the advice given label
Date field should have todays's field as default
add button should be enabled

comments.value: #	Scenario: Validate the disclaimer footer message
#	Given user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
#	When the user selects the disclaimer footer message checkbox along with complete all the mandatory fields
#	Then add button should be enabled

steps.name: user is on ‘Add a sell order’ extended side tray
the user clicks the add button from Add a sell order extended side tray
order should be saved as draft order and should be displayed on the place order screen
user is on the draft order screen
user click the available draft order
add sell order extended side tray should open and user should be able to edit the order
user is on the edit order screen
user changes the different asset or order value
click the update button
updated new changes should be displayed in the draft order screen
user is on the draft order screen
the user clicks the sell button and places the another order
newly placed order should be displayed under the previous order on the draft order screen
user is on the draft order screen
user clicks the close button for any draft order card
confirmation pop-up message should be displayed on the screen

elements.name: Validate the Go back button on the confirmation popup

steps.name: user is can able to view the confirmation pop-up for close order
the user clicks the Go back button
that order should not be closed and order should be displayed on the draft order screen

elements.name: Validate the cancel order button on the confirmation popup

steps.name: user is can able to view the confirmation popup for close order
the user clicks the cancel order button
that particular order should be get disappear from the draft order screen
user is on the draft order screen
the user clicks the preview button from the draft order screen
User should navigate to the preview order screen
transaction summary value on preview order screen and addition of draft orders value should be same
user is on the preview order screen
the user finds before and after portfolio impact of the available units
available units should be reduced based on the order units for that Asset type
Asset name and asset code should be displayed under the before and after impacts of Units

elements.name: Validate the back button on preview order screen

steps.name: user is on the preview order screen
user clicks the back button
User should be navigated to the order draft screen
user is on the draft order screen
the user clicks the preview button from the draft order screen
the user didn’t select the disclaimer checkbox
Confirm order button should be in disable mode
user is on the preview order screen
user clicks the disclaimer link from the preview order screen footer
Disclaimer popup should be display
user is on the preview order screen
User selects the disclaimer checkbox
Order Confirm button should be enabled
user is on the preview order screen
User click the order confirm button after selecting all the mandatory fields
